   <titles>
      <title>Sequence: Illustration</title>
   </titles>
   <body>
      <block>
         <block.body>
            <para>
               <para.body>A sequence <math>
                     <latex>(a_n)</latex>
                  </math> of real numbers associates to each <math>
                     <latex>n\in \NNr</latex>
                  </math> a number in <math>
                     <latex>\RNr</latex>
                  </math>. The graphic below illustrates this process for the first 9 sequence elements.</para.body>
            </para>
            <media xmlns="Theorem" type="image" active="0" inline="0">
               <img xmlns="" src="ims/Sequence.png"/>
            </media>
            <para>
               <para.body>Here we have approximately</para.body>
            </para>
            <ol>
               <li>
                  <para>
                     <para.body>
                        <math>
                           <latex>a_0 \approx 3.6</latex>
                        </math>
                     </para.body>
                  </para>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <para>
                     <para.body>
                        <math>
                           <latex>a_1 \approx 0.5</latex>
                        </math>
                     </para.body>
                  </para>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <para>
                     <para.body>
                        <math>
                           <latex>a_2 \approx -0.3</latex>
                        </math>
                     </para.body>
                  </para>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <para>
                     <para.body>
                        <math>
                           <latex>a_3 \approx 3.8</latex>
                        </math>
                     </para.body>
                  </para>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <para>
                     <para.body>
                        <math>
                           <latex>a_4 = -2</latex>
                        </math>
                     </para.body>
                  </para>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <para>
                     <para.body>
                        <math>
                           <latex>a_5 \approx -4.8</latex>
                        </math>
                     </para.body>
                  </para>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <para>
                     <para.body>
                        <math>
                           <latex>a_6 \approx -2.4</latex>
                        </math>
                     </para.body>
                  </para>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <para>
                     <para.body>
                        <math>
                           <latex>a_7 \approx 0.3</latex>
                        </math>
                     </para.body>
                  </para>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <para>
                     <para.body>
                        <math>
                           <latex>a_8 \approx 4.5</latex>
                        </math>
                     </para.body>
                  </para>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <para>
                     <para.body>
                        <math>
                           <latex>a_9 \approx 4.4</latex>
                        </math>
                     </para.body>
                  </para>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </block.body>
      </block>
      <block>
         <block.body>
            <para>
               <para.body>Note that a sequence might, but need not, display any regularity.</para.body>
            </para>
         </block.body>
      </block>
